Whereas the United States played a key role in brokering the 2005 Comprehensive Peace Agreement
			 that ended the civil war of nearly 40 years, and resulted in South Sudan’s
			 decision by referendum in January 2011 to secede from Sudan;

Whereas what began as a political power struggle became a widespread ethnic battle that tore apart
			 the Sudan People’s Liberation Movement as well as the cabinet and
			 threatened ethnic violence across the country;

Whereas President Kiir and former Vice President Machar have signed three separate peace
			 agreements, including one on June 10, 2014, to form a transitional
			 government within 60 days;

paragraph.text:
emphasizes the need for the Government of South Sudan and the Sudan People's Liberation Movement in
			 Opposition to implement in good faith the cessation of hostilities
